<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="72" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1008,1503]" pageId="16" pageNumber="72">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,1332,1358]" pageId="16" pageNumber="72">Comments</emphasis>
. This species is considered here because 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Roewer" authorityYear="1955" box="[785,976,1332,1358]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Geolycosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="altera">
<emphasis box="[785,976,1332,1358]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="72">Geolycosa altera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was recently (
<bibRefCitation author="Logunov, D. V." box="[1136,1305,1332,1358]" pageId="16" pageNumber="72" pagination="349 - 362" refId="ref12526" refString="Logunov, D. V. (2012) A synopsis of the genus Zyuzicosa Logunov, 2010 (Aranei: Lycosidae). Arthropoda Selecta, 21, 349 - 362. https: // doi. org / 10.15298 / arthsel. 21.4.05" type="journal article" year="2012">Logunov 2012</bibRefCitation>
; World Spi- der 
<bibRefCitation author="World Spider Catalog" box="[194,346,1368,1394]" pageId="16" pageNumber="72" refId="ref14359" refString="World Spider Catalog (2020) World Spider Catalog. Version 21.0. Natural History Museum Bern. Available from: http: // wsc. nmbe. ch (accessed 1 August 2020) https: // doi. org / 10.24436 / 2" type="book" year="2020">Catalog 2020</bibRefCitation>
) placed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", McKay" authorityYear="1979" box="[470,573,1368,1394]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Trochosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[470,573,1368,1394]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="72">Trochosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Although we have not studied the type, this species is adequately illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Logunov, D. V." box="[187,375,1404,1431]" pageId="16" pageNumber="72" pagination="349 - 362" refId="ref12526" refString="Logunov, D. V. (2012) A synopsis of the genus Zyuzicosa Logunov, 2010 (Aranei: Lycosidae). Arthropoda Selecta, 21, 349 - 362. https: // doi. org / 10.15298 / arthsel. 21.4.05" type="journal article" year="2012">Logunov (2012)</bibRefCitation>
. Its peculiarly shaped vulva is exactly the same as that of 
<emphasis box="[1036,1136,1404,1430]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="72">
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Lecigne" authorityYear="2016" box="[1036,1131,1404,1430]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Hogna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferox">H. ferox</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
The female 
<typeStatus box="[1279,1369,1404,1430]" pageId="16" pageNumber="72">allotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Roewer" authorityYear="1955" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Geolycosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atroscopulata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="72">G. atroscopulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a subadult with a well-developed ‘pre-epigyne’. The structure of the epigyne and habitus in the type of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Roewer" authorityYear="1955" box="[182,407,1476,1502]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Lycorma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrichelis">
<emphasis box="[182,407,1476,1502]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="72">Lycorma nigrichelis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are identical to those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Lecigne" authorityYear="2016" box="[684,774,1476,1502]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Hogna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferox">
<emphasis box="[684,774,1476,1502]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="72">H. ferox</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
